139
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:56,000
(Yukawa Keisuke) This is the ward's video distribution channel. I'm telling you about the mayor's job.

140
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:59,000
Um... this place is used for police personnel.

141
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:03,000
(Amishima) Police work is important. But I'm more popular.

142
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:10,000
♬〜

143
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:15,000
I liked it! Make this your disaster response headquarters!

144
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:17,000
(3 people) Huh!?

145
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,000
(Ryukichi) That hanging boy!

146
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,000
Bossy.

147
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,000
(wind chime sound)

148
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:32,000
🔊(Radio) Approaching the collapse site. Be wary of secondary collapse.

149
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:35,000
🔊The person in need of rescue cannot be seen yet.

150
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:38,000
🔊Bottom: Unchanged due to dust. Person in need of rescue cannot be seen.

151
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,000
🔊 Continue to be wary of collapse.

152
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:43,000
(Fire brigade chief) Two students and a female teacher who tried to save them fell into the hole.

153
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:46,000
People are calling out to him from outside, but his safety is unknown.

154
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:48,000
(Rescue Captain) The depth of the hole is about 5 meters.

155
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,000
The cause is thought to be a broken sewage pipe running underground.

156
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,000
Preparations are underway for a search by drone.

157
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:56,000
(Minoru Mukai) Lifelines such as gas and water supplies around the school have been cut off.

158
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:59,000
While coordinating with the Tokyo Metropolitan Government in accordance with the Disaster Countermeasures Basic Act →

159
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:01,000
Establish an emergency response system.

160
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,000
(Rescue Captain) The rescue procedure is trench rescue →

161
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:06,000
Enclose the hole with plywood to prevent dirt and sewage from entering.

162
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:09,000
We are also considering injection of fluidized soil.

163
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,000
This is due to aging infrastructure.

164
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:21,000
Hey.

165
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:27,000
This is due to aging infrastructure.

166
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:32,000
There are many sewer pipes in the ward that have a useful lifespan of over 50 years.

167
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:37,000
Because the previous mayor left it alone! It's the previous mayor's responsibility!

168
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:40,000
But I'm moving.

169
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,000
First in this town! Make this town great!

170
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,000
A man who is like a mass of noise.

171
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:50,000
(Suguro) Such a young person...

172
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:53,000
His shoes were pointy.

173
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,000
It makes me angry.

174
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:59,000
26 years old. The youngest ward mayor in Tokyo.

175
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,000
yes.

176
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,000
(Suguro) Ah, a former talent...

177
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:08,000
``From child actor to politics'' was his selling point, and he became mayor of the ward last year.

178
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Is that why it's so theatrical?

179
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,000
tea! (Mio) Huh?

180
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,000
(Amishima) Tea! (Mio) Cha?

181
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:21,000
Isn't it tea? Why me...

182
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,000
(Amishima) Tea! (Mio) Yes, right now.

183
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:25,000
(Rescue Captain) Video of the drone will appear.

184
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,000
🔊(Radio) Move to locating the person in need of rescue.

185
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:43,000
♬〜

186
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:45,000
(Rescue Captain) It looks like all three are safe!

187
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,000
Momoko-san, could you cut it into smaller pieces?

188
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,000
Ah yes. Ah!

189
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,000
Hey, you can't even cut vegetables!?

190
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:00,000
Because knives can stab people.

191
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,000
Too much detective work.

192
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:05,000
Ah~ Already...

193
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:10,000
That Momoko. Yeah?

194
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,000
Yesterday I...

195
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:15,000
Your mouth is fine, so move your hands.

196
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:19,000
yes. Onigiri.

197
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,000
🖥️(Announcer) This is the scene at night.

198
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,000
🖥️ According to interviews with the people involved, the hole that caved in was 8 meters in diameter.

199
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,000
🖥️ Search by drone →

200
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:31,000
Although it was confirmed that the two students and the teacher who fell into the hole were alive →

201
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:33,000
There is a risk of secondary disaster if you go inside →

202
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:36,000
Police and fire departments are considering rescue options.

203
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,000
Thank you for your hard work.

204
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:45,000
There's nothing strange in the rice ball, right?

205
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,000
Today is pretty normal.

206
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,000
Thank you for your hard work.

207
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,000
Thank you for your hard work.

208
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,000
What about all of you...?

209
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,000
(Sound of wind chimes) Ah...

210
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,000
Is it food rationing?

211
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:05,000
Pork soup with lots of meat. Please fill me up too.

212
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,000
Is it free to refill?

213
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:10,000
Everyone, the gas in your house is turned off.

214
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:13,000
no. I can make rice.

215
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,000
So why don't you cut off your water supply?

216
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
I'm drinking water. Hahaha….

217
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:23,000
I'm sorry, but this is for the rescue workers...

218
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:27,000
Hey, do you know about me?

219
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:32,000
My son's wife won't cook for me.

220
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,000
It's okay.

221
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,000
That's impossible.

222
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,000
Stingy.

223
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:44,000
No, I'm stingy... I'll run out.

224
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:55,000
When you try to enter the hole, the floor around you collapses →

225
00:15:55,000 --> 00:16:00,000
Unreasonable rescue efforts are dangerous because there is a risk of being buried alive.

226
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:05,000
It's already been 10 hours! What can I do!?

227
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:10,000
(Mukai) We are considering countermeasures with the safety of the three people as our top priority.

228
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:16,000
I asked around (Suguro) ward staff and nearby residents...

229
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:19,000
Hey Kuro-san...

230
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:23,000
This time, we're not investigating, we're here for disaster relief.

231
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:25,000
It just happened.

232
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:30,000
...I also heard from school officials.

233
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:38,000
With the declining birthrate, I was wondering why this school opened last year.

234
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:44,000
When I asked about it, the number of children who moved there due to the construction boom in Tawaman was increasing.

235
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:49,000
ah. It appears that construction was halted due to opposition from residents.

236
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:52,000
The ward mayor has restarted construction...

237
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:55,000
Did you hear about that time? Yeah.

238
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:58,000
There are strange rumors from the residents...

239
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:01,000
It seems so. Do you want to find out?

240
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,000
Kuro-san, I was in the second section before I came here.

241
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:06,000
I'm already looking into it.

242
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:12,000
♬〜

243
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:16,000
(cell phone vibration sound)

244
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:20,000
what up?

245
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:23,000
It seems that you have made contact with Section 2.

246
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:28,000
Chief Akase is starting to do something other than giving orders.

247
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:36,000
Chief Akase is starting to do something other than giving orders.

248
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,000
Continue to keep an eye on your brother.

249
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:45,000
I can no longer continue monitoring.

250
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:48,000
My brother knows everything.

251
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:52,000
Are you watching me?

252
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:01,000
You promised to make your wish come true.

253
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:07,000
📞(Shingo) It's your dream.

254
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:22,000
♬〜

255
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:29,000
(Norifumi's voice) It's scary! Brother, help me!

256
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,000
Help me, brother!

257
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:33,000
That's scary, bro!

258
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:36,000
help me! scared!

259
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,000
(cry)

260
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,000
(Enlightenment) Zewen...!

261
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,000
help me…!

262
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:45,000
(Boys) Don't come here.

263
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,000
Stop it!

264
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,000
Stop it! You're crying!

265
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:53,000
(Boy) So noisy! Stop it!

266
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,000
(Boy) Go over there. You're crying!

267
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,000
(Female) I want to go to that hospital.

268
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,000
Ah~ Yes, yes.

269
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:06,000
Here, go straight on this road and go right at the second traffic light.

270
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,000
(Woman) Ah... thank you. Do you understand?

271
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:14,000
Ou. Be careful. (2 people) Hello.

272
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,000
Okay, see you then. bye bye.

273
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:21,000
(Hajime Kurimura) The next time is in 40 minutes...

274
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:41,000
♬〜

275
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:43,000
Brother...

276
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,000
There is something I would like to ask you.

277
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:10,000
Sorry for being so persistent. It happened yesterday...

278
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:14,000
Stop here. Children are waiting to be rescued.

279
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,000
That's right...

280
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,000
(wind chime sound)

281
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:23,000
What happened?

282
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:27,000
I was wondering which tent is ours.

283
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:31,000
Well, this is for those rescue workers to take a break...

284
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,000
Ah, everyone can rest now.

285
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:39,000
Is there a cushion? If the chair is hard, my back hurts.

286
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:42,000
Do you all live nearby?

287
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:47,000
When I'm at home, my grandson treats me like a nuisance.

288
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,000
I don't have a place at home.

289
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:52,000
So please let me stay here.

290
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:55,000
No! Please go back!

291
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,000
Stingy.

292
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:04,000
Hey Ryukichi-kun. That thing to this person...

293
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:08,000
(wind chime sound)

294
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:12,000
Even if I talk to you, you'll understand.

295
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,000
But...

296
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:16,000
No matter what I said to this kid...

297
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,000
Old man.

298
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:22,000
What did you just catch? Did you say old man?

299
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,000
I said sure. Old man.

300
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:28,000
Don't think all the old people are hard of hearing.

301
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:31,000
If anything, these two eyes are 2.0.

302
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:35,000
(Ryukichi) Now it's Jijihara! I'll sue you for Jijihara!

303
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,000
That’s it!

304
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:42,000
There's something I don't like about this too, so I'm irritated.

305
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:45,000
(sigh)

306
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:52,000
The things I hate are the things I hate...

307
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,000
As expected...

308
00:21:55,000 --> 00:22:04,000
♬〜

309
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:07,000
Were you able to rescue him? What do you think?

310
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:10,000
It seems that the positions of teachers and students cannot be accurately determined.

311
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:14,000
Huh!? You saw it in the drone footage earlier!

312
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:17,000
Ask the ward mayor for more details! (Mukai) Yes.

313
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:22,000
The rescue team descended into the hole, but could not find the three people as they had moved →

314
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:26,000
I saw a cavity that was not a sewer pipe extending sideways from the bottom 5 meters below →

315
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:28,000
It seems that it has been confirmed.

316
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:31,000
It is unknown why the cavity exists →

317
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:34,000
It may have been man-made...

318
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:37,000
I don't care about that, please help me quickly!

319
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:39,000
If someone dies, I'll be responsible!

320
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:44,000
Experts say it's unusual for the ground and the gym floor to collapse at the same time.

321
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:48,000
There may have been a flaw in the design or construction.

322
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:53,000
You can't use it. Fired.

323
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,000
(Amishima) Please call someone else.

324
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:58,000
ᗕYes!

325
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:16,000
♬〜

326
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:22,000
He's a terrible mayor. What does it mean to fire someone who works hard?

327
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:27,000
Could you tell me a little bit about it?

328
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:34,000
♬〜

329
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:41,000
♬〜

330
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:44,000
Excuse me. I brought you a snack.

331
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:51,000
Please let me know if you need anything. I'll bring it right away.

332
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:54,000
(Director) Come on, come on, come on, this is the next room.

333
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:57,000
Are you a family member of a disaster victim? Hey... you guys!

334
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:59,000
(Director) Excuse me, but may I ask you a question?

335
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:02,000
Please let me know! What happened? Details Details!

336
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:06,000
(crying) What...?

337
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:10,000
Ah! This... this person is the father of the child who fell into the hole!

338
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,000
That's right! Please tell me more details!

339
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,000
We'll talk about anything. Outside!

340
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:17,000
Please go outside. Sorry everyone! Sorry to bother you!

341
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:19,000
(cry)

342
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:24,000
sorry. A child... It was difficult, wasn't it? What happened?

343
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:32,000
♬〜

344
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:37,000
You guys will be arrested for trespassing on a building!

345
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:40,000
Yes, yes, hurry up and get out! Wait... are you serious!

346
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:43,000
Look! Go quickly! worst!

347
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:45,000
ᗕ(Director) Don't take pictures, don't take pictures, don't take pictures...!

348
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:53,000
♬〜

349
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,000
Parents, it's been a long time coming.

350
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:10,000
Yeah. I'll bring a nap blanket from car 3.

351
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:15,000
You probably won't be able to sleep, but I think you should lie down for a while.

352
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,000
That's good. help.

353
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:34,000
♬〜

354
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:38,000
yes. Yes, I understand.

355
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,000
(Maruchi) Mayor...

356
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:48,000
The man from the construction company is coming.

357
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:55,000
Everyone come out. I want to be alone!

358
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:57,000
yes!

359
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:03,000
♬〜

360
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,000
cormorant~….

361
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:07,000
(sound of door opening)

362
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,000
(yawn)

363
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:11,000
what?

364
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:16,000
I apologize for taking up your time.

365
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,000
Something I was worried about.

366
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:23,000
I explained this to Mr. Mori, the secretary, when we were planning the construction of the school.

367
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:25,000
This land used to be...

368
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:29,000
That guy was fired. Because he wrote bad things about me in his secret account.

369
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:32,000
Also to Mr. Kaga from the Public Facilities Division...

370
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:36,000
I told him not to come to the office. I cry easily when I get angry.

371
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:41,000
(Male) Ah... ah~….

372
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:43,000
(sigh)

373
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:52,000
♬〜

374
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:54,000
(Teruhiko Nemoto) Hey, beautiful sister!

375
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:58,000
Met looks good on you. He looks like a skilled craftsman at a construction site.

376
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:01,000
(Mio) Are you happy to be praised or not?

377
00:27:01,000 --> 00:27:03,000
I'm not praising you.

378
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:06,000
(Yu Masuda) I've been watching the news and it seems like the rescue efforts are taking a lot of time.

379
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:08,000
Let the buds go!

380
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:11,000
Tie a rope to him and make him jump into the hole. Even if I fail, I'll pick up my bones.

381
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,000
Don't be silly! There's a child inside.

382
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:15,000
It was!

383
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:19,000
So what? I'm busy with an incident here.

384
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:23,000
There's something I'd like you to look into.

385
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:26,000
I don't have time for that. Do your best to rescue them.

386
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:28,000
See you then. Excuse me.

387
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:33,000
Rescue alone wasn't enough.

388
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:39,000
♬〜

389
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:41,000
Is it an incident?

390
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:52,000
♬〜

391
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:54,000
(Announcer's voice) Looks like there's some movement on the scene!

392
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:57,000
It is said that the surrounding floor collapsed and debris fell to the bottom of the hole!

393
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:59,000
The safety of the three people is unknown! It's a dangerous situation!

394
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:01,000
ᗕEvacuate immediately! Hurry!

395
00:28:05,066 --> 00:28:07,066
(Souichiro Midorikawa) Don't move?

396
00:28:07,066 --> 00:28:13,066
Yeah. If you move it, the ground will vibrate and affect the cave-in area.

397
00:28:13,066 --> 00:28:15,066
Are you stuck...

398
00:28:15,066 --> 00:28:18,066
Mecha old man, what should I do?

399
00:28:18,066 --> 00:28:20,066
That's right...

400
00:28:20,066 --> 00:28:25,066
Raise the tire with a jack and place a steel plate underneath.

401
00:28:25,066 --> 00:28:29,066
The only way to move the car is to spread out the weight of the car. (Swan) I see.

402
00:28:29,066 --> 00:28:33,066
Okay! Let me bring the equipment. (Swan) Yes, please.

403
00:28:33,066 --> 00:28:35,066
Oh, I'm already in trouble!

404
00:28:35,066 --> 00:28:38,066
Alright, let me meet the ward chief! Please go back!

405
00:28:38,066 --> 00:28:40,066
Don't interfere with the rescue work!

406
00:28:40,066 --> 00:28:43,066
(Mitsui) I have something to tell the mayor! This is an important topic!

407
00:28:43,066 --> 00:28:46,066
The gym floor collapsed, right?

408
00:28:46,066 --> 00:28:49,066
I can't watch it anymore! Let me meet the ward chief!

409
00:28:49,066 --> 00:28:52,066
(Midorikawa) What happened to Bud? Ah, thank you for your hard work.

410
00:28:52,066 --> 00:28:56,066
These people have been making a lot of noise since yesterday.

411
00:28:56,066 --> 00:29:00,066
This kid won't listen to us!

412
00:29:00,066 --> 00:29:04,066
A kid!? If not a kid, then a baby?

413
00:29:04,066 --> 00:29:06,066
Noisy old man!

414
00:29:06,066 --> 00:29:09,066
(Mizue) You too will become an old man soon.

415
00:29:09,066 --> 00:29:12,066
I can't watch it anymore! All right, let me meet the ward chief.

416
00:29:12,066 --> 00:29:14,066
Okay, I'll listen.

417
00:29:14,066 --> 00:29:16,066
oh! If you're an old man, you'll understand.

418
00:29:16,066 --> 00:29:19,066
Who is the old man? (Ryukichi) It's an old man!

419
00:29:19,066 --> 00:29:23,066
Grandpa graduated a long time ago. This is my second time as a young man.

420
00:29:23,066 --> 00:29:26,066
What did the old man say? (Midorikawa) That's why I'm not an old man.

421
00:29:26,066 --> 00:29:28,066
No, no, it's an old man.

422
00:29:28,066 --> 00:29:31,066
The old man... there's a traffic jam...

423
00:29:31,066 --> 00:29:33,066
(Ryukichi) It's old man! (Mitsui) It's old man.

424
00:29:40,066 --> 00:29:42,066
(Amishima) Stop the camera!

425
00:29:42,066 --> 00:29:44,066
(operation sound)

426
00:29:44,066 --> 00:29:50,066
(Amishima) What are you doing? Quickly rescue me! Are you going to fire all of you?

427
00:29:50,066 --> 00:29:53,066
If you say you're going to fire me, I'll really do it!

428
00:29:53,066 --> 00:29:55,066
Ou. Ah, old mecha.

429
00:29:55,066 --> 00:29:57,066
Ah, old mecha. (Maruchi) Who is it?

430
00:29:57,066 --> 00:30:00,066
Ah... I'm a former detective from the First Investigative Division.

431
00:30:00,066 --> 00:30:04,066
After that, I worked in the equipment department maintaining police vehicles.

432
00:30:04,066 --> 00:30:07,066
Now that he has retired, he maintains this car.

433
00:30:07,066 --> 00:30:09,066
Why did you come in?

434
00:30:09,066 --> 00:30:11,066
Who are you?

435
00:30:11,066 --> 00:30:14,066
what? This is Mayor Amishima.

436
00:30:14,066 --> 00:30:16,066
Ah, I see.

437
00:30:16,066 --> 00:30:22,066
Mayor-san, I heard this from an old man who has known this area well for a long time.

438
00:30:22,066 --> 00:30:25,066
My name is Ryukichi and I live in Kakubacho 2-chome.

439
00:30:25,066 --> 00:30:28,066
Oh... please, please. Please sit down.

440
00:30:28,066 --> 00:30:31,066
(Midorikawa) That was 81 years ago.

441
00:30:31,066 --> 00:30:38,066
In March 1945, during the Pacific War, there was a major air raid on Tokyo.

442
00:30:38,066 --> 00:30:41,066
(Amishima) Huh? What are you talking about?

443
00:30:41,066 --> 00:30:43,066
Let's listen.

444
00:30:43,066 --> 00:30:46,066
More than 300 American bombers arrived.

445
00:30:46,066 --> 00:30:50,066
More than 320,000 incendiary bombs →

446
00:30:50,066 --> 00:30:54,066
They were dropped in Tokyo, mainly in the downtown area.

447
00:30:54,066 --> 00:31:05,066
♬〜

448
00:31:05,066 --> 00:31:10,066
(Midorikawa) Overnight, Tokyo became a burnt field →

449
00:31:10,066 --> 00:31:13,066
More than 100,000 people died.

450
00:31:15,066 --> 00:31:19,066
(Midorikawa) This is land that has been owned by a zaibatsu since before the war.→

451
00:31:19,066 --> 00:31:24,066
Apparently there was a communal air raid shelter for the townspeople during the war.

452
00:31:24,066 --> 00:31:29,066
It is an underground evacuation site to protect lives from bombs.

453
00:31:30,066 --> 00:31:33,066
Nearly 50 people from the town were evacuated.

454
00:31:33,066 --> 00:31:36,066
That cavity still remains →

455
00:31:36,066 --> 00:31:40,066
It could no longer bear the weight of the gymnasium and collapsed.

456
00:31:40,066 --> 00:31:43,066
I see. So there is a cavity 5 meters below.

457
00:31:43,066 --> 00:31:46,066
There was a hole in the ground and the floor of the gymnasium collapsed as a result.

458
00:31:50,066 --> 00:31:52,066
(operation sound)

459
00:31:52,066 --> 00:31:54,066
Mr. Ryukichi.

460
00:31:54,066 --> 00:31:56,066
What about the hole?

461
00:31:56,066 --> 00:31:58,066
Ah...

462
00:31:59,066 --> 00:32:01,066
(Firefighter Chief) This is it.

463
00:32:02,066 --> 00:32:05,066
(Firefighter Chief) Can you write the structure inside?

464
00:32:05,066 --> 00:32:09,066
Ah... that's right.

465
00:32:09,066 --> 00:32:13,066
This is where the entrance to the air raid shelter was.

466
00:32:14,066 --> 00:32:20,066
If you go down the hole, you will see something like this... If you go down this way →

467
00:32:20,066 --> 00:32:22,066
Oh yeah yeah!

468
00:32:22,066 --> 00:32:28,066
There was a well-built evacuation site in this area.

469
00:32:28,066 --> 00:32:34,066
As long as the teachers and children are safe, I'll be here.

470
00:32:34,066 --> 00:32:36,066
I will issue rescue instructions! thank you!

471
00:32:36,066 --> 00:32:39,066
please! please.

472
00:32:43,066 --> 00:32:45,066
What are you talking about?

473
00:32:46,066 --> 00:32:48,066
It's about an air raid shelter.

474
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:50,066
What? that.

475
00:32:50,066 --> 00:32:52,066
This is a story about a time of war.

476
00:32:52,066 --> 00:32:54,066
war? (Midorikawa) Yes, but.

477
00:32:54,066 --> 00:32:56,066
Is there a war here?

478
00:32:57,066 --> 00:33:02,066
Mayor-san, are you kidding?

479
00:33:02,066 --> 00:33:05,066
What do you mean there was a war?

480
00:33:05,066 --> 00:33:09,066
Was there a war in Japan? Like in Ukraine?

481
00:33:13,066 --> 00:33:16,066
What's going on with this guy?

482
00:33:16,066 --> 00:33:20,066
Many of my generation don't really know about the war.

483
00:33:20,066 --> 00:33:23,066
But so far...

484
00:33:23,066 --> 00:33:28,066
I've heard something about it, but I'm not interested in past history.

485
00:33:28,066 --> 00:33:33,066
You don't need to know that... Is it even on the internet?

486
00:33:33,066 --> 00:33:40,066
Apparently, when the plan to build this school came up, these old men appealed directly to the ward.

487
00:33:40,066 --> 00:33:45,066
They wanted it to be preserved as a war ruin without building a school.

488
00:33:45,066 --> 00:33:50,066
I heard it, but I didn't understand what it was saying...

489
00:33:50,066 --> 00:33:54,066
Don't you really know there was a war? You studied at school.

490
00:33:55,066 --> 00:34:00,066
I haven't gone to school. Actor's work is busy.

491
00:34:02,066 --> 00:34:08,066
But studying is not the only important thing! What's wrong with not knowing about war?

492
00:34:18,066 --> 00:34:20,066
Mecha old man...

493
00:34:22,066 --> 00:34:24,066
Sigh….

494
00:34:27,066 --> 00:34:29,066
Look!

495
00:34:30,066 --> 00:34:34,066
🖥️(Rescue member) Found the child and teacher! It's safe!

496
00:34:34,066 --> 00:34:36,066
🖥️ We will start the lifting work! Sigh….

497
00:34:36,066 --> 00:34:38,066
it was good….

498
00:34:38,066 --> 00:34:48,066
♬〜

499
00:34:48,066 --> 00:34:50,066
Hey, turn the camera!

500
00:34:50,066 --> 00:34:52,066
Turn it!

501
00:34:53,066 --> 00:34:56,066
No, you...! Pan on my face from the monitor screen!

502
00:34:59,066 --> 00:35:02,066
Alright! Well done!

503
00:35:02,066 --> 00:35:06,066
You followed my orders and rescued me well!

504
00:35:06,066 --> 00:35:08,066
